OL,3,CNorthern Ireland police allegedly
OL,4,Cspied on BBC journalist
OL,6,FCommenting on the claims of police
OL,7,Fsurveillance against him, Mr Kearney
OL,8,Fsaid: "I am concerned that the police
OL,9,Fmay have attempted to identify sources
OL,10,Fof information within a programme that
OL,11,Fwas actually about the independence of
OL,12,Fthe office of the Police Ombudsman.
OL,14,F"Journalists must be free to carry out
OL,15,Ftheir work without fear that the
OL,16,Fpolice may secretly try to identify
OL,17,Fsources and I am determined to find
OL,18,Fout what happened."
