OL,3,CNorthern Ireland police allegedly
OL,4,Cspied on BBC journalist
OL,6,FLast month, the PSNI delivered a
OL,7,Freport on surveillance of journalists
OL,8,Fand lawyers to its oversight body, the
OL,9,FNorthern Ireland Policing Board.
OL,10,FHowever, the document on surveillance
OL,11,Fpractices will not be made public.
OL,13,FThe board's human rights adviser will
OL,14,Fbe granted access to material the
OL,15,Freport is based on, and PSNI Chief
OL,16,FConstable Jon Boutcher has committed
OL,17,Fto the production of a second report,
OL,18,Fwhich will be made public.
